{"recipe_desc": "We don't often eat hamburgers, but when we do, we love this simple recipe. You can also grill this hamburgers outside if you prefer, but the stove top is quick and easy.", "recipe_category": ["Entrees"], "recipe_image": ["/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers.jpg"], "recipe_total_time": ["PT30M"], "recipe_published_time": ["Jul 27, 2012"], "image_urls": ["http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers.jpg"], "recipe_ingredients": ["1 slice of ", "3 tablespoons whole milk", "3 teaspoons steak or A-1 sauce", "1 medium clove garlic, minced", "\u00be teaspoon salt", "\u00be teaspoon ground black pepper", "1 \u00bd pounds of 90 percent lean ground chuck", "3 teaspoons vegetable oil", "sliced cheese (optional)", "4 "], "recipe_prep_time": ["PT15M"], "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<title>Stove Top Burgers Recipe - MakeBetterFood.com</title>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html;charset=utf-8\" />\n<link href=\"http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Brawler\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n<link href=\"/css/style.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n<!--[if lte IE 7]>\n<link href=\"/css/ie7.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\"/>\n<![endif]-->\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />\n<link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"MakeBetterFood.com - Recipes, Learn How to Cook Amazing Food\" href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/MakeBetterFood\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Stove Top Burgers Recipe\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"food\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers.jpg\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"MakeBetterFood.com\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"We don't often eat hamburgers, but when we do, we love this simple recipe. You can also grill this hamburgers outside if you prefer, but the stove top is quick and easy.\"/>\n<meta property=\"fb:admins\" content=\"5711219\" />\n<!-- For Google Custom Site Search -->\n<!--\n<PageMap>\n<DataObject type=\"action\">\n<Attribute name=\"label\" value=\"Print Recipe\"/>\n<Attribute name=\"url\" value=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/pdfs/stove-top-burgers.pdf\"/>\n<Attribute name=\"class\" value=\"print\"/>\n</DataObject>\n<DataObject type=\"thumbnail\">\n<Attribute name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers.jpg\"/>\n<Attribute name=\"width\" value=\"400\"/>\n<Attribute name=\"height\" value=\"267\"/>\n</DataObject>\n</PageMap>\n-->\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container_12\">\n<div class=\"topbar\">\n<div class=\"topbar-inner\">\n<h3><a href=\"/\"><img src=\"/img/makebetterfood.png\" alt=\"\"/>Make Better Food</a></h3>\n<ul class=\"nav\">\n<li><a href=\"/about/\">About</a></li>\n<li class=\"dropdown\">\n<a href=\"/recipes/\" class=\"dropdown-toggle\">Recipes</a>\n<ul class=\"dropdown-menu\">\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/appetizers/\">Appetizers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/breakfast/\">Breakfast</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/homemade/\">Homemade Ingredients</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/drinks/\">Drinks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/jam-and-jelly/\">Jams and Jellies</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/side-dishes/\">Side Dishes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/entrees/\">Entrees</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/soups/\">Soups</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/pasta/\">Pasta</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/pizza/\">Pizza</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/bread/\">Breads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/desserts/\">Desserts</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"/subscribe/\">Subscribe</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"search\">\n<form action=\"/search/\" method=\"get\">\n<input type=\"text\" name=\"q\" id=\"q\" required=\"required\" />\n<input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"Search\"/>\n</form>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"background\">\n<div class=\"fader\"></div>\n<img src=\"/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers_large.jpg\" alt=\"Stove Top Burgers\" />\n</div>\n<div class=\"grid_12\">\n<div class=\"recipe\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Recipe\">\n<h1 itemprop=\"name\">Stove Top Burgers</h1>\n<div class=\"socialButtons\">\n<div class=\"fb-like\" data-send=\"false\" data-href=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"105\" data-show-faces=\"false\" data-action=\"like\"></div>\n<div class=\"pinterest\">\n<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.makebetterfood.com%2Frecipes%2Fstove-top-burgers%2F&media=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers_large.jpg&description=Stove%20Top%20Burgers\" class=\"pin-it-button\" count-layout=\"horizontal\">Pin It</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"print\"><a href=\"/pdfs/stove-top-burgers.pdf\" onclick=\"logPrintEvent('Stove Top Burgers');\"><img src=\"/img/icons/print.png\" alt=\"Print\" /></a><a href=\"/pdfs/stove-top-burgers.pdf\" onclick=\"logPrintEvent('Stove Top Burgers');\">Print or download (PDF)</a></div>\n</div>\n<ul class=\"breadcrumbs\">\n<li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/\">Recipes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/entrees/\"><span itemprop=\"recipeCategory\">Entrees</span></a></li>\n<li>Stove Top Burgers</li>\n</ul>\n<div itemprop=\"description\" class=\"description\">We don't often eat hamburgers, but when we do, we love this simple recipe. You can also grill this hamburgers outside if you prefer, but the stove top is quick and easy.</div>\n<div class=\"stats\">\n<ul>\n<li>Prep: <meta itemprop=\"prepTime\" value=\"PT15M\"/>15 min</li>\n<li>Cook: <meta itemprop=\"cookTime\" value=\"PT15M\"/>15 min</li>\n<li>Total: <meta itemprop=\"totalTime\" value=\"PT30M\"/>30 min</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeYield\">Serves 4</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"steps\">\n<div class=\"right\">\n<a href=\"/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers_large.jpg\"><img class=\"polaroid\" src=\"/recipes/stove-top-burgers/stove-top-burgers.jpg\" alt=\"Stove Top Burgers\" itemprop=\"image\"/></a>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 slice of <a href='/recipes/american-sandwich-bread/'>high-quality white sandwich bread</a></li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Chop bread into 1/4-inch pieces and remove any hard parts of crust.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">3 tablespoons whole milk</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Place bread pieces in a medium bowl. Add milk and mash with a folk until formed into a thick paste.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">3 teaspoons steak or A-1 sauce</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 medium clove garlic, minced</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">&frac34; teaspoon salt</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">&frac34; teaspoon ground black pepper</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Add steak sauce, garlic, salt, and pepper to bread mixture. Stir to combine.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 &frac12; pounds of 90 percent lean ground chuck</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Using you hands, break ground beef into small chunks over the bread mixture and gently mix with your hands until bread mixture has combined with beef.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Divide beef mixture into four equal portions and form into a patty with your hands. The resulting patty should be about 4 inches in diameter and 3/4-inch thick. Using your thumb, press gently but firmly in the center of the patty to make a small indentation.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">3 teaspoons vegetable oil</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Heat oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until just beginning to smoke.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Cook patties, indentation side up, until well-browned, about 5 minutes. Flip patties with a spatula and continue cooking, about 4 minutes for medium-well or 5 minutes for well-done.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">sliced cheese (optional)</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">If you want a cheeseburger, place sliced cheese on top of patties after you flip them. Cover skillet with a loose fitting lid to help cheese melt.</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">4 <a href='/recipes/hamburger-buns/'>hamburger buns or rolls</a></li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Serve burgers on buns with desired toppings.</li>\n<li class=\"subheader\">Make Ahead</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Extra patties can be wrapped in wax paper, placed in a plastic bag, and frozen for up to 2 weeks. To thaw, remove patties and place in a single layer on a baking sheet and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes prior to cooking.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"footnote\">\n<div class=\"logo\">MakeBetterFood.com</div>\nFrom MakeBetterFood.com. <time itemprop=\"datePublished\" datetime=\"2012-07-27\">Jul 27, 2012</time>. (http://makebetterfood.com/recipes/stove-top-burgers/). Adapted from <a href='http://www.cooksillustrated.com/recipes/detail.asp?docid=8016&parentdocid=10089'>Cook's Illustrated</a>. (January 2007.)\n</div>\n<!-- Microformat Ingredients -->\n<ul class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 slice of <a href='/recipes/american-sandwich-bread/'>high-quality white sandwich bread</a></li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 tablespoons whole milk</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 teaspoons steak or A-1 sauce</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 medium clove garlic, minced</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac34; teaspoon salt</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac34; teaspoon ground black pepper</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 &frac12; pounds of 90 percent lean ground chuck</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 teaspoons vegetable oil</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">sliced cheese (optional)</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">4 <a href='/recipes/hamburger-buns/'>hamburger buns or rolls</a></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Microformat Steps -->\n<ol class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Chop bread into 1/4-inch pieces and remove any hard parts of crust.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Place bread pieces in a medium bowl. Add milk and mash with a folk until formed into a thick paste.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Add steak sauce, garlic, salt, and pepper to bread mixture. Stir to combine.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Using you hands, break ground beef into small chunks over the bread mixture and gently mix with your hands until bread mixture has combined with beef.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Divide beef mixture into four equal portions and form into a patty with your hands. The resulting patty should be about 4 inches in diameter and 3/4-inch thick. Using your thumb, press gently but firmly in the center of the patty to make a small indentation.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Heat oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until just beginning to smoke.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Cook patties, indentation side up, until well-browned, about 5 minutes. Flip patties with a spatula and continue cooking, about 4 minutes for medium-well or 5 minutes for well-done.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">If you want a cheeseburger, place sliced cheese on top of patties after you flip them. Cover skillet with a loose fitting lid to help cheese melt.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Serve burgers on buns with desired toppings.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Extra patties can be wrapped in wax paper, placed in a plastic bag, and frozen for up to 2 weeks. To thaw, remove patties and place in a single layer on a baking sheet and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes prior to cooking.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"notPrinted\">\n<div class=\"grid_12\">\n<div class=\"recipe\">\n<h4>Related Equipment or Ingredients</h4>\n<div class=\"pushTop10 clearfix polarioidSummaryRow\">\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://ww